{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":3393,"text":"Science,"},{"time":4621,"text":"science has allowed us to know so much"},{"time":7958,"text":"about the far reaches of the universe,"},{"time":10984,"text":"which is at the same time tremendously important"},{"time":14179,"text":"and extremely remote,"},{"time":16245,"text":"and yet much, much closer,"},{"time":18704,"text":"much more directly related to us,"},{"time":20795,"text":"there are many things we don't really understand."},{"time":23263,"text":"And one of them is the extraordinary"},{"time":25392,"text":"social complexity of the animals around us,"},{"time":28718,"text":"and today I want to tell you a few stories"},{"time":30734,"text":"of animal complexity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":32742,"text":"But first, what do we call complexity?"},{"time":36092,"text":"What is complex?"},{"time":37579,"text":"Well, complex is not complicated."},{"time":41006,"text":"Something complicated comprises many small parts,"},{"time":44454,"text":"all different, and each of them"},{"time":46899,"text":"has its own precise role in the machinery."},{"time":50003,"text":"On the opposite, a complex system"},{"time":52814,"text":"is made of many, many similar parts,"},{"time":55455,"text":"and it is their interaction"},{"time":57463,"text":"that produces a globally coherent behavior."},{"time":60783,"text":"Complex systems have many interacting parts"},{"time":64619,"text":"which behave according to simple, individual rules,"},{"time":68045,"text":"and this results in emergent properties."},{"time":71394,"text":"The behavior of the system as a whole"},{"time":73282,"text":"cannot be predicted"},{"time":74950,"text":"from the individual rules only."},{"time":77102,"text":"As Aristotle wrote,"},{"time":78912,"text":"the whole is greater than the sum of its parts."},{"time":81972,"text":"But from Aristotle, let's move onto"},{"time":84434,"text":"a more concrete example of complex systems."}]},{"cues":[{"time":88124,"text":"These are Scottish terriers."},{"time":90080,"text":"In the beginning, the system is disorganized."},{"time":93831,"text":"Then comes a perturbation: milk."},{"time":97632,"text":"Every individual starts pushing in one direction"},{"time":101482,"text":"and this is what happens."},{"time":104791,"text":"The pinwheel is an emergent property"},{"time":107617,"text":"of the interactions between puppies"},{"time":109520,"text":"whose only rule is to try to keep access to the milk"},{"time":113430,"text":"and therefore to push in a random direction."}]},{"cues":[{"time":117037,"text":"So it's all about finding the simple rules"},{"time":121012,"text":"from which complexity emerges."},{"time":123770,"text":"I call this simplifying complexity,"},{"time":126710,"text":"and it's what we do at the chair of systems design"},{"time":128845,"text":"at ETH Zurich."},{"time":130822,"text":"We collect data on animal populations,"},{"time":134527,"text":"analyze complex patterns, try to explain them."},{"time":138338,"text":"It requires physicists who work with biologists,"},{"time":140957,"text":"with mathematicians and computer scientists,"},{"time":143680,"text":"and it is their interaction that produces"},{"time":146500,"text":"cross-boundary competence"},{"time":148214,"text":"to solve these problems."},{"time":149792,"text":"So again, the whole is greater"},{"time":152064,"text":"than the sum of the parts."},{"time":153464,"text":"In a way, collaboration"},{"time":155614,"text":"is another example of a complex system."}]},{"cues":[{"time":159105,"text":"And you may be asking yourself"},{"time":160981,"text":"which side I'm on, biology or physics?"},{"time":163798,"text":"In fact, it's a little different,"},{"time":165909,"text":"and to explain, I need to tell you"},{"time":167498,"text":"a short story about myself."},{"time":169840,"text":"When I was a child,"},{"time":171567,"text":"I loved to build stuff, to\ncreate complicated machines."},{"time":175676,"text":"So I set out to study electrical engineering"},{"time":178413,"text":"and robotics,"},{"time":179965,"text":"and my end-of-studies project"},{"time":182058,"text":"was about building a robot called ER-1 --"},{"time":184984,"text":"it looked like thisâ€”"},{"time":186914,"text":"that would collect information from its environment"},{"time":189285,"text":"and proceed to follow a white line on the ground."},{"time":192783,"text":"It was very, very complicated,"},{"time":195162,"text":"but it worked beautifully in our test room,"},{"time":198146,"text":"and on demo day, professors had \nassembled to grade the project."},{"time":201607,"text":"So we took ER-1 to the evaluation room."},{"time":204509,"text":"It turned out, the light in that room"},{"time":206819,"text":"was slightly different."},{"time":208638,"text":"The robot's vision system got confused."},{"time":210969,"text":"At the first bend in the line,"},{"time":212730,"text":"it left its course, and crashed into a wall."},{"time":216469,"text":"We had spent weeks building it,"},{"time":218556,"text":"and all it took to destroy it"},{"time":220229,"text":"was a subtle change in the color of the light"},{"time":222885,"text":"in the room."},{"time":224481,"text":"That's when I realized that"},{"time":225996,"text":"the more complicated you make a machine,"},{"time":228323,"text":"the more likely that it will fail"},{"time":230362,"text":"due to something absolutely unexpected."},{"time":232925,"text":"And I decided that, in fact,"},{"time":234755,"text":"I didn't really want to create complicated stuff."},{"time":237768,"text":"I wanted to understand complexity,"},{"time":240710,"text":"the complexity of the world around us"},{"time":242698,"text":"and especially in the animal kingdom."}]},{"cues":[{"time":245103,"text":"Which brings us to bats."},{"time":248423,"text":"Bechstein's bats are a common\nspecies of European bats."},{"time":251474,"text":"They are very social animals."},{"time":252887,"text":"Mostly they roost, or sleep, together."},{"time":256178,"text":"And they live in maternity colonies,"},{"time":257857,"text":"which means that every spring,"},{"time":259397,"text":"the females meet after the winter hibernation,"},{"time":262655,"text":"and they stay together for about six months"},{"time":264744,"text":"to rear their young,"},{"time":267230,"text":"and they all carry a very small chip,"},{"time":270035,"text":"which means that every time one of them"},{"time":271906,"text":"enters one of these specially equipped bat boxes,"},{"time":274963,"text":"we know where she is,"},{"time":276606,"text":"and more importantly,"},{"time":277775,"text":"we know with whom she is."},{"time":280338,"text":"So I study roosting associations in bats,"},{"time":284032,"text":"and this is what it looks like."},{"time":286477,"text":"During the day, the bats roost"},{"time":288919,"text":"in a number of sub-groups in different boxes."},{"time":291223,"text":"It could be that on one day,"},{"time":293152,"text":"the colony is split between two boxes,"},{"time":295372,"text":"but on another day,"},{"time":296672,"text":"it could be together in a single box,"},{"time":298913,"text":"or split between three or more boxes,"},{"time":301229,"text":"and that all seems rather erratic, really."},{"time":304156,"text":"It's called fission-fusion dynamics,"},{"time":307359,"text":"the property for an animal group"},{"time":309072,"text":"of regularly splitting and merging"},{"time":311250,"text":"into different subgroups."}]},{"cues":[{"time":312911,"text":"So what we do is take all these data"},{"time":315473,"text":"from all these different days"},{"time":317135,"text":"and pool them together"},{"time":318639,"text":"to extract a long-term association pattern"},{"time":321256,"text":"by applying techniques with network analysis"},{"time":323761,"text":"to get a complete picture"},{"time":325382,"text":"of the social structure of the colony."},{"time":327919,"text":"Okay? So that's what this picture looks like."},{"time":332184,"text":"In this network, all the circles"},{"time":334578,"text":"are nodes, individual bats,"},{"time":337355,"text":"and the lines between them"},{"time":338938,"text":"are social bonds, associations between individuals."},{"time":342602,"text":"It turns out this is a very interesting picture."},{"time":345280,"text":"This bat colony is organized"},{"time":347262,"text":"in two different communities"},{"time":349130,"text":"which cannot be predicted"},{"time":350969,"text":"from the daily fission-fusion dynamics."},{"time":353218,"text":"We call them cryptic social units."},{"time":356768,"text":"Even more interesting, in fact:"},{"time":358384,"text":"Every year, around October,"},{"time":360748,"text":"the colony splits up,"},{"time":362309,"text":"and all bats hibernate separately,"},{"time":365007,"text":"but year after year,"},{"time":366468,"text":"when the bats come together again in the spring,"},{"time":369541,"text":"the communities stay the same."}]},{"cues":[{"time":372131,"text":"So these bats remember their friends"},{"time":374851,"text":"for a really long time."},{"time":376681,"text":"With a brain the size of a peanut,"},{"time":379155,"text":"they maintain individualized,"},{"time":381280,"text":"long-term social bonds,"},{"time":383422,"text":"We didn't know that was possible."},{"time":385146,"text":"We knew that primates"},{"time":386905,"text":"and elephants and dolphins could do that,"},{"time":389473,"text":"but compared to bats, they have huge brains."},{"time":392101,"text":"So how could it be"},{"time":394500,"text":"that the bats maintain this complex,"},{"time":396451,"text":"stable social structure"},{"time":398139,"text":"with such limited cognitive abilities?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":401671,"text":"And this is where complexity brings an answer."},{"time":404560,"text":"To understand this system,"},{"time":406701,"text":"we built a computer model of roosting,"},{"time":409498,"text":"based on simple, individual rules,"},{"time":411516,"text":"and simulated thousands and thousands of days"},{"time":413951,"text":"in the virtual bat colony."},{"time":415970,"text":"It's a mathematical model,"},{"time":418094,"text":"but it's not complicated."},{"time":420048,"text":"What the model told us is that, in a nutshell,"},{"time":423146,"text":"each bat knows a few other colony members"},{"time":426332,"text":"as her friends, and is just slightly more likely"},{"time":428820,"text":"to roost in a box with them."},{"time":431330,"text":"Simple, individual rules."},{"time":433774,"text":"This is all it takes to explain"},{"time":435486,"text":"the social complexity of these bats."}]},{"cues":[{"time":437875,"text":"But it gets better."},{"time":439593,"text":"Between 2010 and 2011,"},{"time":442441,"text":"the colony lost more than two thirds of its members,"},{"time":445894,"text":"probably due to the very cold winter."},{"time":448880,"text":"The next spring, it didn't form two communities"},{"time":452024,"text":"like every year,"},{"time":453295,"text":"which may have led the whole colony to die"},{"time":455498,"text":"because it had become too small."},{"time":457593,"text":"Instead, it formed a single, cohesive social unit,"},{"time":462966,"text":"which allowed the colony to survive that season"},{"time":465698,"text":"and thrive again in the next two years."},{"time":468802,"text":"What we know is that the bats"},{"time":470580,"text":"are not aware that their colony is doing this."},{"time":473487,"text":"All they do is follow simple association rules,"},{"time":477033,"text":"and from this simplicity"},{"time":478382,"text":"emerges social complexity"},{"time":480823,"text":"which allows the colony to be resilient"},{"time":483663,"text":"against dramatic changes\nin the population structure."},{"time":486644,"text":"And I find this incredible."}]},{"cues":[{"time":489338,"text":"Now I want to tell you another story,"},{"time":491422,"text":"but for this we have to travel from Europe"},{"time":492977,"text":"to the Kalahari Desert in South Africa."},{"time":496025,"text":"This is where meerkats live."},{"time":498052,"text":"I'm sure you know meerkats."},{"time":499552,"text":"They're fascinating creatures."},{"time":501658,"text":"They live in groups with a\nvery strict social hierarchy."},{"time":504647,"text":"There is one dominant pair,"},{"time":506106,"text":"and many subordinates,"},{"time":507488,"text":"some acting as sentinels,"},{"time":509202,"text":"some acting as babysitters,"},{"time":510539,"text":"some teaching pups, and so on."},{"time":512436,"text":"What we do is put very small GPS collars"},{"time":515757,"text":"on these animals"},{"time":517282,"text":"to study how they move together,"},{"time":519157,"text":"and what this has to do with their social structure."},{"time":522874,"text":"And there's a very interesting example"},{"time":524364,"text":"of collective movement in meerkats."},{"time":527080,"text":"In the middle of the reserve which they live in"},{"time":529447,"text":"lies a road."},{"time":530656,"text":"On this road there are cars, so it's dangerous."},{"time":533889,"text":"But the meerkats have to cross it"},{"time":536173,"text":"to get from one feeding place to another."},{"time":538747,"text":"So we asked, how exactly do they do this?"},{"time":543498,"text":"We found that the dominant female"},{"time":545334,"text":"is mostly the one who leads the group to the road,"},{"time":547955,"text":"but when it comes to crossing it, crossing the road,"},{"time":551227,"text":"she gives way to the subordinates,"},{"time":553578,"text":"a manner of saying,"},{"time":555355,"text":"\"Go ahead, tell me if it's safe.\""},{"time":558037,"text":"What I didn't know, in fact,"},{"time":559701,"text":"was what rules in their behavior the meerkats follow"},{"time":562843,"text":"for this change at the edge of the group to happen"},{"time":565768,"text":"and if simple rules were sufficient to explain it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":569618,"text":"So I built a model, a model of simulated meerkats"},{"time":573609,"text":"crossing a simulated road."},{"time":575522,"text":"It's a simplistic model."},{"time":577394,"text":"Moving meerkats are like random particles"},{"time":580234,"text":"whose unique rule is one of alignment."},{"time":582456,"text":"They simply move together."},{"time":584862,"text":"When these particles get to the road,"},{"time":588046,"text":"they sense some kind of obstacle,"},{"time":589988,"text":"and they bounce against it."},{"time":592072,"text":"The only difference"},{"time":593228,"text":"between the dominant female, here in red,"},{"time":595270,"text":"and the other individuals,"},{"time":596755,"text":"is that for her, the height of the obstacle,"},{"time":599309,"text":"which is in fact the risk perceived from the road,"},{"time":601814,"text":"is just slightly higher,"},{"time":603763,"text":"and this tiny difference"},{"time":605424,"text":"in the individual's rule of movement"},{"time":607262,"text":"is sufficient to explain what we observe,"},{"time":609708,"text":"that the dominant female"},{"time":612268,"text":"leads her group to the road"},{"time":613702,"text":"and then gives way to the others"},{"time":615372,"text":"for them to cross first."},{"time":618235,"text":"George Box, who was an English statistician,"},{"time":621886,"text":"once wrote, \"All models are false,"},{"time":624848,"text":"but some models are useful.\""},{"time":626907,"text":"And in fact, this model is obviously false,"},{"time":630104,"text":"because in reality, meerkats are\nanything but random particles."},{"time":634072,"text":"But it's also useful,"},{"time":635709,"text":"because it tells us that extreme simplicity"},{"time":638458,"text":"in movement rules at the individual level"},{"time":641816,"text":"can result in a great deal of complexity"},{"time":644167,"text":"at the level of the group."},{"time":646105,"text":"So again, that's simplifying complexity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":650161,"text":"I would like to conclude"},{"time":651609,"text":"on what this means for the whole species."},{"time":654426,"text":"When the dominant female"},{"time":656090,"text":"gives way to a subordinate,"},{"time":657656,"text":"it's not out of courtesy."},{"time":659773,"text":"In fact, the dominant female"},{"time":661280,"text":"is extremely important for the cohesion of the group."},{"time":663799,"text":"If she dies on the road, the whole group is at risk."},{"time":667311,"text":"So this behavior of risk avoidance"},{"time":669547,"text":"is a very old evolutionary response."},{"time":672348,"text":"These meerkats are replicating an evolved tactic"},{"time":676217,"text":"that is thousands of generations old,"},{"time":678450,"text":"and they're adapting it to a modern risk,"},{"time":680864,"text":"in this case a road built by humans."},{"time":684189,"text":"They adapt very simple rules,"},{"time":686584,"text":"and the resulting complex behavior"},{"time":688873,"text":"allows them to resist human encroachment"},{"time":691829,"text":"into their natural habitat."}]},{"cues":[{"time":694277,"text":"In the end,"},{"time":696079,"text":"it may be bats which change their social structure"},{"time":698779,"text":"in response to a population crash,"},{"time":701163,"text":"or it may be meerkats"},{"time":702562,"text":"who show a novel adaptation to a human road,"},{"time":705764,"text":"or it may be another species."},{"time":708449,"text":"My message here -- and it's not a complicated one,"},{"time":711242,"text":"but a simple one of wonder and hope --"},{"time":714006,"text":"my message here is that animals"},{"time":717099,"text":"show extraordinary social complexity,"},{"time":719523,"text":"and this allows them to adapt"},{"time":721964,"text":"and respond to changes in their environment."},{"time":725445,"text":"In three words, in the animal kingdom,"},{"time":728213,"text":"simplicity leads to complexity"},{"time":730987,"text":"which leads to resilience."}]},{"cues":[{"time":732470,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":734754,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":750694,"text":"Dania Gerhardt: Thank you very much, Nicolas,"},{"time":752647,"text":"for this great start. Little bit nervous?"},{"time":755926,"text":"Nicolas Perony: I'm okay, thanks."},{"time":757570,"text":"DG: Okay, great. I'm sure a \nlot of people in the audience"},{"time":760030,"text":"somehow tried to make associations"},{"time":761894,"text":"between the animals you were talking about --"},{"time":763718,"text":"the bats, meerkats -- and humans."},{"time":765774,"text":"You brought some examples:"},{"time":766982,"text":"The females are the social ones,"},{"time":768717,"text":"the females are the dominant ones,"},{"time":770430,"text":"I'm not sure who thinks how."},{"time":772103,"text":"But is it okay to do these associations?"},{"time":774998,"text":"Are there stereotypes you can confirm in this regard"},{"time":777798,"text":"that can be valid across all species?"},{"time":781071,"text":"NP: Well, I would say there are also"},{"time":782674,"text":"counter-examples to these stereotypes."},{"time":784626,"text":"For examples, in sea horses or in koalas, in fact,"},{"time":787766,"text":"it is the males who take care of the young always."},{"time":791464,"text":"And the lesson is that it's often difficult,"},{"time":796505,"text":"and sometimes even a bit dangerous,"},{"time":798257,"text":"to draw parallels between humans and animals."},{"time":800929,"text":"So that's it."},{"time":803035,"text":"DG: Okay. Thank you very much for this great start."},{"time":805881,"text":"Thank you, Nicolas Perony."}]}]}